commitResults.messageTitle: Display sample Vehicle List on app GUI.

commitResults.messageBody: Fill command generates new incidents. Operator needs to input caller number. Operator will be prompted for incident description and location. Operator, incidentDateTime, and incidentId details will be autofilled.
Fill command fields now include location and description fields, on top of the callerNumber. The incident is now successfully added to the list of incidents in the IMS.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add three 'Status' states to incidents - draft, complete, final.

commitResults.messageBody: Issues fixed by removing unused imports.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix code quality issues pertaining to unused variables.
Fix code quality issues with unused variables.

commitResults.messageBody:
Mode 1: submit without parameters - lists completed incident reports ready for submission.
Mode 2: submit with parameter i/INDEX - submits specified incident report.
Summary of incident filling and submitting feature.

commitResults.messageTitle: Append new incidents to front of list.

commitResults.messageBody:
- Make 'fill' command work on all drafts (complete and incomplete drafts).
- Set index taken in by 'fill' and 'submit' commands to refer to the last shown incident list on the IMS GUI.
- Use SLAP to improve code quality of 'Find' and 'Submit' commands.
- Generalise 'ListIncidentsCommand' to carry out the listing functionalities of 'Find' and 'Submit' commands.

- Make date-time format of incident reports more human reader-friendly.
- Add unit tests to ensure incident date time formats are enforced.
- Remove redundant constructor.
- Modify JsonAdaptedIncident to be compatible with changes to Incident class.

- Add 'status' badge to visualise incident status changes brought about by `fill` and `submit` commands.
- Add description, caller number, operator, location, and date time fields in a readable and presentable way to the IncidentListCard.

commitResults.messageBody: - Change Incident toString() method to return IncidentId instead of Incident description. This change necessitated changes in editCommandTest.
